%description:
TCP Fast Open (RFC 7413) F6.1: bounds the client-role cookie cache
(fastopenCookieCacheSize). A pure Tcp-module-level cache test rather than a
full network module test -- the eviction policy is exercised entirely
through setFastOpenCookie()/getFastOpenCookie(), with no protocol
interaction needed, so a direct unit test (same live-module-instantiation
pattern as tcp_fastopen_cookie_gen_1.test) is a more precise and simpler fit
than standing up three real TCP handshakes to three distinct destinations
through the module-test network harness.

Sets fastopenCookieCacheSize=2, then inserts cookies for 3 distinct
addresses. Eviction is documented as "arbitrary, not LRU" (see Tcp.cc):
concretely, std::map<L3Address,...>::begin() evicts the numerically smallest
still-cached address, not the first-inserted one. With addr1 < addr2 < addr3
and insertion order addr1, addr2, addr3, only addr1 and addr2 are in the map
when addr3 triggers eviction, so addr1 (the smaller of the two) is evicted.
That happens to coincide with "oldest inserted" in this particular scenario,
but this note is spelling out that it's a same-address-ordering coincidence
of this test's chosen addresses, not a guarantee the implementation
provides.

Falsification: same 3-insert sequence with the default fastopenCookieCacheSize
(1024, i.e. effectively unbounded here) -- all three must remain cached.

%includes:
#include "inet/transportlayer/tcp/Tcp.h"
#include "inet/networklayer/common/L3Address.h"
#include "inet/networklayer/contract/ipv4/Ipv4Address.h"

%global:

using namespace inet;
using namespace inet::tcp;

static Tcp *makeTcpMain(const char *name, int cacheSize)
{
    cModuleType *moduleType = cModuleType::get("inet.transportlayer.tcp.Tcp");
    Tcp *tcpMain = check_and_cast<Tcp *>(moduleType->create(name, getSimulation()->getSystemModule()));
    tcpMain->par("fastopenCookieCacheSize").setIntValue(cacheSize);
    tcpMain->finalizeParameters();
    tcpMain->callInitialize();
    return tcpMain;
}

%activity:

L3Address addr1(Ipv4Address("10.0.0.1"));
L3Address addr2(Ipv4Address("10.0.0.2"));
L3Address addr3(Ipv4Address("10.0.0.3"));

{
    // Bounded: fastopenCookieCacheSize=2.
    Tcp *tcpMain = makeTcpMain("tcpMainBounded", 2);
    tcpMain->setFastOpenCookie(addr1, {0x01});
    tcpMain->setFastOpenCookie(addr2, {0x02});
    tcpMain->setFastOpenCookie(addr3, {0x03}); // triggers eviction (cache was at capacity 2)

    std::vector<uint8_t> cookie;
    EV << "bounded: addr1 cached=" << (tcpMain->getFastOpenCookie(addr1, cookie) ? "yes" : "no") << "\n";
    EV << "bounded: addr2 cached=" << (tcpMain->getFastOpenCookie(addr2, cookie) ? "yes" : "no") << "\n";
    EV << "bounded: addr3 cached=" << (tcpMain->getFastOpenCookie(addr3, cookie) ? "yes" : "no") << "\n";

    tcpMain->deleteModule();
}

{
    // Falsification: default fastopenCookieCacheSize (1024) on the same 3-insert
    // sequence -- well under the bound, so nothing should be evicted.
    Tcp *tcpMain = makeTcpMain("tcpMainDefault", 1024);
    tcpMain->setFastOpenCookie(addr1, {0x01});
    tcpMain->setFastOpenCookie(addr2, {0x02});
    tcpMain->setFastOpenCookie(addr3, {0x03});

    std::vector<uint8_t> cookie;
    EV << "unbounded: addr1 cached=" << (tcpMain->getFastOpenCookie(addr1, cookie) ? "yes" : "no") << "\n";
    EV << "unbounded: addr2 cached=" << (tcpMain->getFastOpenCookie(addr2, cookie) ? "yes" : "no") << "\n";
    EV << "unbounded: addr3 cached=" << (tcpMain->getFastOpenCookie(addr3, cookie) ? "yes" : "no") << "\n";

    tcpMain->deleteModule();
}

EV << ".\n";

%contains: stdout
bounded: addr1 cached=no
bounded: addr2 cached=yes
bounded: addr3 cached=yes
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%contains: stdout
unbounded: addr1 cached=yes
unbounded: addr2 cached=yes
unbounded: addr3 cached=yes
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%contains: stdout
.
